a)` → `T | null`\n- `softDelete(id)` → `void`\n- `delete(id)` → `void`\n- `count(options?)` → `number`\n\n**BaseService** (`base.service.ts`):\n- `findByIdOrFail(id, relations?)` → `T` (throws `NotFoundException`)\n- `findAll(options?)` → `T[]`\n- `create(data)` → `T`\n- `update(id, data)` → `T | null`\n- `remove(id)` → `void` (soft deletes)\n- `delete(id)` → `void` (hard deletes)\n\n**BaseController** (`base.controller.ts`):\n- `POST /` → create resource\n- `GET /` → findAll (with optional `page`/`limit` query)\n- `GET /:id` → findOne\n- `PATCH /:id` → update\n- `DELETE /:id` → remove\n\n---\n\n### 4. Decorators (`backend/src/core/decorators/index.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nexport { Public, IS_PUBLIC_KEY } from './public.decorator';\nexport { Roles, ROLES_KEY } from './roles.decorator';\nexport { CurrentUser } from './current-user.decorator';\nexport { ApiSwagger } from './api-swagger.decorator';\nexport { ApiResponseData } from './api-response-data.decorator';\n```\n\n- **`@Public()`** — Marks a route as public (bypasses JWT auth)\n- **`@Roles('admin')`** — Marks required roles (string array; consumes `role` or `roles` from `request.user`)\n- **`@CurrentUser()`** / `@CurrentUser('id')` — Extracts user from request\n- **`@ApiSwagger(...)`** — Composite decorator for auto-generating Swagger docs\n\n---\n\n### 5. Guards (`backend/src/core/guards/index.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nexport { JwtAuthGuard } from './jwt-auth.guard';\nexport { RolesGuard } from './roles.guard';\nexport { JwtStrategy } from './jwt.strategy';\n```\n\n**JwtAuthGuard**: Reads `@Public()` metadata to skip auth; otherwise validates JWT cookie (`access_token`).\n\n**RolesGuard**: Reads `@Roles(...)` metadata; compares `request.user.role` (single string) or `request.user.roles` (array) against required roles.\n\n**JwtStrategy**: Extracts JWT from `access_token` cookie or Bearer header; returns `{ id: payload.sub, email: payload.email, role: payload.role }`.\n\n**Important**: Only `JwtAuthGuard` is registered globally in `main.ts` as a global guard. `RolesGuard` is NOT registered globally — it must be used per-controller/per-route or registered at the module level. However, looking at how the `PropertyController` uses `@Roles('admin')` without any explicit `RolesGuard` registration, it seems the project may rely on a different pattern or the `RolesGuard` is registered elsewhere. Check this before implementing.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Shared DTOs (`backend/src/shared/dtos/`)\n\n**Exports** (`index.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport { ResponsePayloadDto, ErrorDetailDto, SuccessResponseDto, ErrorResponseDto, PaginationMetaDto, PaginatedResponseDto } from './response-payload.dto';\nexport { PaginationDto } from './pagination.dto';\n```\n\n**`PaginationDto`** — Has optional `page` (int, min 1), `limit` (int, min 1, max 100), `sortBy` (string), `sortOrder` ('ASC' | 'DESC'), `search` (string).\n\n**`ResponsePayloadDto<T>`** — Envelope: `{ success, statusCode, message, data?, error?, timestamp?, path? }`.\n\n**`PaginationMetaDto`** — `{ page, limit, total, totalPages, hasNextPage, hasPreviousPage }`.\n\n**`PaginatedResponseDto<T>`** — `extends ResponsePayloadDto<T[]>` with additional `meta: PaginationMetaDto`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Pattern Analysis - The Properties Module (Best Reference)\n\nSince amenities are closely related to properties, this is the **most relevant module pattern**.\n\n#### File structure:\n```\nbackend/src/modules/properties/\n├── dto/                          # EMPTY (no DTOs defined)\n├── entities/\n│   ├── amenity.entity.ts\n│   ├── property-amenity.entity.ts\n│   ├── property-photo.entity.ts\n│   └── property.entity.ts\n├── property.controller.ts\n├── property.module.ts\n├── property.repository.ts\n└── property.service.ts\n```\n\n#### Key Observations:\n\n**Controller** (`property.controller.ts`) — does NOT extend `BaseController`:\n- Uses `@Controller('properties')` (NOT passing a path prefix to each method)\n- Uses `@Public()` for public routes, `@Roles('admin')` for admin routes\n- Manually constructs response envelope: `return { message: '...', data: ... }`\n- The `TransformInterceptor` wraps responses that don't have a `success` field, and skips wrapping those that do. But the properties controller does NOT include `success` in its return, so the interceptor wraps it.\n- Uses `@Query() query: any` (not typed DTOs)\n- Uses `@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string` for UUID validation\n- Methods: `search()`, `findOne()`, `create()`, `update()`, `archive()`\n\n**Service** (`property.service.ts`) — extends `BaseService<Property>`:\n```typescript\n@Injectable()\nexport class PropertyService extends BaseService<Property> {\n  constructor(private readonly propertyRepository: PropertyRepository) {\n    super(propertyRepository, 'Property');\n  }\n  // Custom methods: search(), findByIdOrFail(), archive()\n}\n```\n\n**Repository** (`property.repository.ts`) — extends `BaseRepository<Property>`:\n```typescript\n@Injectable()\nexport class PropertyRepository extends BaseRepository<Property> {\n  constructor(@InjectRepository(Property) repository: Repository<Property>) {\n    super(repository);\n  }\n  // Custom: search() with complex filtering\n}\n```\n\n**Module** (`property.module.ts`):\n```typescript\n@Module({\n  imports: [TypeOrmModule.forFeature([Property, PropertyPhoto, Amenity, PropertyAmenity])],\n  controllers: [PropertyController],\n  providers: [PropertyRepository, PropertyService],\n  exports: [PropertyService],\n})\nexport class PropertyModule {}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Existing E2E Test for Amenities\n\n**`/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/test/e2e/amenities.e2e-spec.ts`** (354 lines)\n\nThis is a **RED PHASE** test — it expects the amenities module to be implemented. Key patterns:\n\n**Imports it expects:**\n```typescript\nimport { Amenity } from '../../src/modules/properties/entities/amenity.entity';\n// RED PHASE: import { AmenitiesModule } from '../../src/modules/properties/amenities.module';\n```\n\n**Setup pattern:**\n1. Creates test app via `createTestApp()` (optionally passing feature modules — currently empty `[]`)\n2. Seeds users and generates admin/renter tokens\n3. Seeds amenities via `seedTestAmenities(dataSource)` from `property.fixture.ts`\n\n**Endpoints tested:**\n\n| Method | Path | Auth | Status Codes |\n|--------|------|------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/api/amenities` | Public | 200 |\n| `POST` | `/api/amenities` | Admin | 201, 400, 401, 403, 409 |\n| `PATCH` | `/api/amenities/:id` | Admin | 200, 400, 401, 403, 404, 409 |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/amenities/:id` | Admin | 200, 400, 401, 403, 404 |\n\n**Expected request/response shapes:**\n\n- **POST body**: `{ name: string (1-50 chars), icon: string (1-50 chars) }`\n- **PATCH body**: `{ name?: string, icon?: string }` (partial update)\n- **Response shape**: `{ success, statusCode, message, data, timestamp, path }` (TransformInterceptor pattern)\n- **Success messages**: `'Amenities retrieved successfully'`, `'Amenity created successfully'`, `'Amenity updated successfully'`, `'Amenity deleted successfully'`\n\n**Test fixtures** (`backend/test/fixtures/property.fixture.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport const testAmenities: Array<{ name: string; icon: string }> = [\n  { name: 'Parking', icon: 'parking' },\n  { name: 'Gym', icon: 'gym' },\n  { name: 'Pool', icon: 'pool' },\n  { name: 'Pet Friendly', icon: 'pet' },\n];\n\nexport async function seedTestAmenities(dataSource: DataSource): Promise<Amenity[]> {\n  const repository = dataSource.getRepository(Amenity);\n  const amenities = repository.create(testAmenities);\n  return repository.save(amenities);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. PROJECT_API.md - Amenities Section (lines 1083-1138)\n\n```\n### Amenities (Admin)\n\n| Method | Path              | Description         | Auth   |\n|--------|-------------------|---------------------|--------|\n| GET    | `/api/amenities`  | List all amenities  | Public |\n| POST   | `/api/amenities`  | Create a new amenity| Admin  |\n| PATCH  | `/api/amenities/:id` | Update an amenity | Admin  |\n| DELETE | `/api/amenities/:id` | Delete an amenity | Admin  |\n```\n\n**GET /api/amenities**: Returns `{ statusCode: 200, data: [{ id, name }, ...] }`\n\n**POST /api/amenities**: Body `{ name: string (2-50 chars, unique) }`. Returns `{ statusCode: 201, message: \"Amenity created\", data: { id, name } }`. Error responses: 400, 401, 403, 409.\n\n---\n\n### 10. PROJECT_DATABASE.md - Amenity Entity (lines 172-192)\n\n```\nTable: amenities\n├── id          UUID PK (auto-generated)\n├── name        varchar(50) UNIQUE, NOT NULL\n├── icon        varchar(50) NOT NULL\n├── created_at  timestamp NOT NULL\n├── updated_at  timestamp NOT NULL\n├── deleted_at  timestamp NULLABLE (soft delete)\n\nIndexes: UNIQUE on name\n\nRelationships:\n  belongsToMany → Property via property_amenities junction\n\nSoft delete: ENABLED on `amenities`\n```\n\nThe junction table **`property_amenities`**:\n- Composite PK: `(property_id, amenity_id)`\n- Both columns are UUIDs with FK + ON DELETE CASCADE\n- `@Index` on `amenity_id`\n\n---\n\n### 11. MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml\n\n**Only has one entry** — for `inquiries` (scoping GET for renter vs admin). **No amenities-related entries.**\n\n---\n\n### 12. Enums (`backend/src/common/enums/`)\n\n| File | Enum | Values |\n|------|------|--------|\n| `role.enum.ts` | `RoleEnum` | `RENTER = 'renter'`, `ADMIN = 'admin'` |\n| `user-status.enum.ts` | `UserStatusEnum` | `ACTIVE = 'active'`, `SUSPENDED = 'suspended'` |\n| `property-type.enum.ts` | `PropertyTypeEnum` | `APARTMENT`, `HOUSE`, `CONDO`, `TOWNHOUSE`, `STUDIO` |\n| `inquiry-status.enum.ts` | `InquiryStatusEnum` | `NEW = 'new'`, `READ = 'read'`, `RESPONDED = 'responded'` |\n\n**Barrel export** (`backend/src/common/enums/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport { RoleEnum } from './role.enum';\nexport { UserStatusEnum } from './user-status.enum';\nexport { PropertyTypeEnum } from './property-type.enum';\nexport { InquiryStatusEnum } from './inquiry-status.enum';\n```\n\nNo amenity-specific enum exists.\n\n---\n\n### 13. App Module Registration (`backend/src/app.module.ts`)\n\n```typescript\n@Module({\n  imports: [\n    ConfigModule.forRoot({ isGlobal: true }),\n    TypeOrmModule.forRoot({\n      type: 'sqlite',\n      database: 'nestfind.sqlite',\n      entities: [__dirname + '/modules/**/entities/*.entity{.ts,.js}'],\n      synchronize: true,\n    }),\n    AuthModule, UserModule, PropertyModule, FavoriteModule, InquiryModule, AdminModule,\n  ],\n})\nexport class AppModule {}\n```\n\nThe Amenity entity is **auto-discovered** via the glob pattern: `modules/**/entities/*.entity{.ts,.js}`. So as long as the entity file is placed under any module's `entities/` directory, it will be registered automatically.\n\n---\n\n### 14. Test Infrastructure (`backend/test/`)\n\n**`test/setup/test-app.factory.ts`** — Creates a test app with:\n- In-memory SQLite (better-sqlite3)\n- All entities manually listed (User, RefreshToken, PasswordResetToken, Property, PropertyPhoto, Amenity, PropertyAmenity, Favorite, Inquiry)\n- Global prefix: `/api`\n- Global pipes: ValidationPipe (whitelist, forbidNonWhitelisted, transform)\n- Global filters: AllExceptionsFilter, HttpExceptionFilter\n- Global interceptors: LoggingInterceptor, TransformInterceptor\n- Accepts optional `featureModules: any[]` for registering new modules\n\n**`test/setup/test-database.ts`** — Clean database between tests using reverse-order DELETE.\n\n**`test/fixtures/auth.fixture.ts`** — Uses mock tokens: `mock-access-token-{userId}-{role}`. Sets JWT via cookie: `{ Cookie: \\`access_token=${token}\\` }`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary: Recommended Implementation Pattern\n\nBased on all the patterns above, the amenities module should follow the **properties module pattern**:\n\n```\nbackend/src/modules/amenities/\n├── dto/\n│   ├── create-amenity.dto.ts     # { name (2-50, string), icon (2-50, string) }\n│   └── update-amenity.dto.ts     # Partial<CreateAmenityDto>\n├── entities/\n│   └── amenity.entity.ts         # ALREADY EXISTS in properties/entities/ — MOVE IT HERE\n├── amenity.controller.ts\n├── amenity.module.ts\n├── amenity.repository.ts\n├── amenity.service.ts\n└── index.ts\n```\n\n**Key decisions to make:**\n1. **Move** `Amenity` entity from `properties/entities/` to `amenities/entities/` (it will still be auto-discovered by the glob pattern)\n2. The `PropertyAmenity` junction entity stays in `properties/entities/` (it belongs with properties)\n3. Controller should use `@Public()` for GET, `@Roles('admin')` for POST/PATCH/DELETE\n4. Service should extend `BaseService<Amenity>` for reuse of base CRUD\n5. Repository should extend `BaseRepository<Amenity>`\n6. Register the module in `app.module.ts`\n7. The e2e test at `backend/test/e2e/amenities.e2e-spec.ts` is already written and provides the exact spec to implement against\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_1bca1f119ffeyTL4sJ2zgRapo6","sessionId":"ses_1bca19c06ffe96H3ajr38UvC3u","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"opencode-go"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore amenities codebase","time":{"start":1779246719996,"end":1779247084339}},"id":"prt_e435e3bb8001ue9ij79cLmhRvC","sessionID":"ses_1bca1f119ffeyTL4sJ2zgRapo6","messageID":"msg_e435e13f60015GO5oYfBlDJ4Lu"}}
